data.description: What to say but WOW! This house is so perfect that a few personal touches will make it home for the new owner! As you pull up to your new home, you know you have found a gem. This home flows easy with the kitchen right off the garage, so bringing the groceries in is very convenient! The wood floors are beautiful thru out the home, while the ceramic tile will be easy to clean in the wet areas. Its a split plan, so master bedroom has privacy. The other bedrooms, which are very good size, can be closed off from the rest of the house by a pocket door when not in use. The cook can still visit or watch the game while preparing dinner. The screened back porch offers a 4 person spa, a bonus room, and a view out over the fenced back yard to watch the sunset as you relax, with a open patio great for grilling. Go out the back screened door to the shop that includes a fan for ventilation and roll up door. There is also room to store your tools. The tankless hot water means hot water on demand! The Generac panel in the over sized 2 car garage making it easy to run essential items during a storm, two more cars can park in the driveway. In the evening, go for a walk after dinner and enjoy the breeze coming up the hill. You are close to shopping, theatre, hospital, doctor's offices, parks, and within a hour to downtown Tampa, Lakeland or Ocala. You are within 2 hours or less from numerous beaches and (anyone up for scalloping?) places to put your boat in the water for more fun. There is always something going on downtown in Dade City or Zephyrhills, so you will have plenty to do. Come view this home while you can. It could be your last forever home! Call for your appointment today.
